Dior introduces the modern day interpretation of Christian Dior's Lucky Star. The couturier believed in signs of luck, and so does @diormakeup: Stay tuned to discover the lucky shades of the new Dior Addict shimmering star heart lipstick!

#diormakeup #dioraddictstellarshine #dioraddict

Christian Dior believed in the signs of Destiny. In 1946, the couturier chanced upon a metal star lying on the ground of a Parisian crosswalk and took it as a sign of fate. Today, the house of Dior carries his legacy by infusing his Lucky Star into the heart of the new Dior Addict Stellar Halo Shine Lipstick, coming soon!
• 
#diormakeup #dioraddictstellarshine #dioraddict

Christian Dior believed he had a lucky star, looking over him and guiding his destiny. Today, the house of Dior pays tribute to the couturier's lucky charm with a new lipstick creation by @peterphilipsmakeup, Creative and Image Director of Dior Makeup.

GLITTER - This Holiday season, discover an artistic collaboration between @peterphilipsmakeup, Creative & Image Director of Dior Makeup, the Choreographer @jordandrobson and the French Duo of movie Directors @studio_letiquette. 
A visual BIG BANG may be the best way to describe what the GLITTER video is to its creators: a true artistic odyssey like a cosmic trip that brings us back to the origins of the universe. “When Jordan talked to me about a project he wanted to do, I was sold from the moment he showed me an iconic picture by Guy Bourdin of two people covered from head to toe in tiny black cristals. I’ve been wanting to do a video project with glitter and movement for a while and this concept came in perfect timing. At Dior we are open to give a platform to young, dynamic talents. By bringing together Jordan, Studio l’Etiquette and Hajiba Fahmy magic was created . A wonderful synergy between light, darkness, movement, music and the magic of sparkles resulted in this mesmerising video that, for a moment, takes you on a voyage of beauty and dream.” Peter Philips, Creative & Image Director of Dior Makeup.
📷@studio_letiquette
Choreography @jordandrobson 
Makeup @peterphilipsmakeup 
Dancer @hajibafahmy

Recognizable for their XXL square shape, the #DiorStellaire sunglasses complete the silhouette with their refined edge. Harnessing Dior’s expertise and savoir-faire, the frames designed by @MariaGraziaChiuri are meticulously shaped in the House’s atelier in Italy.
© @PolBaril

Several different production steps are required to achieve the timeless and elegant tortoiseshell finish of the latest #DiorStellaire sunglasses by @MariaGraziaChiuri. First, a film is applied to the entire frame before the motif is subtly transferred onto the metal thanks to an innovative heating process. Click on the link in our bio to discover more about this virtuoso creation.
© @PolBaril

With their distinctive oversized square shape and slightly softened edges, the iconic #DiorStellaire sunglasses are unveiled in a new tortoiseshell version requiring unique #DiorSavoirFaire, part of the #DiorCruise 2020 collection by @MariaGraziaChiuri. Stay tuned to step into our Atelier and discover the process behind their creation.
© @PolBaril

In the 'Flash!' series by photographer @BenHassett for #DiorMagazine N°29, check out @PeterPhilipsmakeup's festive make-up looks for #DiorBeauty, featuring glitter, red lips and golden accents on the eyes.

In her 'Dazzling Black' series for the latest issue of #DiorMagazine, @JuliaHetta captures @MariaGraziaChiuri's Autumn-Winter 2019-2020 #DiorCouture creations against an architectural backdrop evoking the salons at 30 Avenue Montaigne, the setting for the show. Explore the collection's main inspiration, the caryatids: feminine statues decorating Paris edifices, pillars that seem to poetically bear the weight of the world, with their streamlined curves evoking ancient Greek temples.

'Monochromes' – photographer @BrigitteNiedermair's latest series for #DiorMagazine – portrays @VictoiredeCastellane's largest ever collection, 'Gem Dior', featuring 99 high jewelry pieces and marking #DiorJoaillerie's 20th anniversary. This chromatic fairy tale was conceived as a unique story of stones and colors, its name conjuring a play on words between 'gem' in English and 'j'aime' in French – meaning, of course, 'I love...'

Ever attuned to world cultures, Korean artist Jia Lee offers her vision of nature and emotion in sketches of dream gardens that come together like a bouquet in the 4th edition of #DiorLadyArt. Sumptuous daffodils and other blossoms seem almost real in her series of #LadyDior handbags. 
Photo by @YoonooKim

Hand-craftsmanship and technology unite to illustrate Dior's avant-garde spirit in the 4th edition of #DiorLadyArt. See how the Portuguese artist @JoanaVasconcelosatelier transposed her earlier work, 'Coeur de Paris', onto the iconic #LadyDior bag. An illuminated gem of innovation, this unique piece pays tribute to Monsieur Dior's favorite red — "the color of life", as he called it — and one of his favorite lucky symbols. 
Photo by @_Moura.Simao_

What’s the relationship between geometry and architecture? Design and museology? Urban planning and art? For the 4th edition of #DiorLadyArt, Mexican architect and artist Eduardo Terrazas addresses all of those ideas and brings his very personal visual language to the iconic #LadyDior handbag.
Photo by @rrodalva

For its 4th edition, @MickaleneThomas returns to #DiorLadyArt for a second time, unveiling a #LadyDior inspired by the charms of a stroll through Claude Monet's beloved gardens at Giverny. A breathtaking blend of embroidered leather and dazzling beadwork embellish a 'Lady Dior' created in homage to Monsieur Dior's love of flowers. Click on the link in our bio for more details!
Photo by @Fumi_Nagasaka

@RaqibShawstudio brings his whimsical and enchanting world to the 4th edition of #DiorLadyArt. Two creations, featuring a starry night sky and supernatural magnolia trees, tell a fantastical tale through chimerical interpretations of the garden at Monsieur Dior's childhood home in Granville, Normandy.
Photo by @JoMetsonScott

See how the Chinese artist Wang Guangle brought his captivating abstract style and signature "Coffin Paint" series to the #LadyDior bag in the 4th edition of #DiorLadyArt. In this video, admire a harmonious irregularity that reprises the ocean's waves, a poetic allusion to life's ebb and flow. To see the full series of this year's 'Dior Lady Art' project, click on the link in our bio.
Photo by @LiKai
